metadata.description:
a generative artwork by Juhani HalkomÃ¤ki

Celebrating my one year fxhash anniversary. The piece is based on my first project on fxhash, the Reflector. In this piece I continued the exploration on rays and reflection in 2D space. The end result is a colorful and fragile artwork with a hint of melancholy.

metadata.name: Our Tune #14
metadata.description:
A love song from an engine that has never heard one. Our Tune tells a four part story of two people's time together and sometimes apart. Do not expect sweetness, though it may happen.

Operation: Touch once to unmute, then let it play through or touch again to cycle.

[[[Best with headphones]]]

Gen Version: Love Song Engine 1 (LSE-1)
License: CC BY-NC 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/deed.en_GB

metadata.name: Annum #8463
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Puxadinho #27
metadata.description:
"Puxadinho" is an expression used in Brazil to refer to the expansion of a house, often without planning, just by "pulling" more built area.

Generally practiced in more peripheral neighborhoods, this annexed construction happens vertically, due to lack of space on the land. 


For this piece I've used p5.js and scribble library

metadata.name: Mind docks sorting station #241
metadata.description:
in an altered state,
order tries to get a grasp,
architect is dreaming

#12
experimental vintage series

press "C" to turn on/off outlines
press "V" to turn on/off blocks, if present
press "B" to turn on/off rotation
press "N" to reload with different layout, 3 iterations to cycle through

press "UP arrow" to increase render scale multiplier by x1 (maximum is x4, default is x2)
press "DOWN arrow" to decrease render scale multiplier by x1

press "S" to save png in live view
